Steve Gardner <gardner@silas-0.cc.monash.edu.au> wrote:
> Ross Morgan-Linial wrote:
> >
> >Please read the later part of that paragraph. The 24 VT+P-Note 
> >estimated maximum is a _maximum_, not a reasonable estimate. That 
> >gives us a total of 2-4 VTs and P-Notes per player per week *before* 
> >accounting for churches, which are intended to sap a few VTs per 
> >player per week from the system.
> 
> They will only have that effect if people spend Ergs to build them.
> Personally, I wouldn't waste my Ergs building Churches, since I
> can avoid Blots by paying my bills on time. Churches don't even
> have a guaranteed income of Indulgences; they merely increase your
> chances of getting one randomly distributed to you. Thanks, but I'd
> rather take the guaranteed VT income of a Farm, or perhaps, in an
> Erg-scarce environment, a Mine. I suspect most Players will think
> likewise.

A player who builds three Churches will get nearly half of the 
Indulgences distributed. Then, whenever anyone gets Blots, about half 
of the Indulgences will go to that player. The player with the Blots 
will then be stuck with PI until he pays the Indulgence-holder's 
price. Seems like a nifty racket to me, unless Agorans stop breaking 
Rules.

> >BTW, the original Plots proto was intended for an environment in 
> >which Officer salaries were replaced with some other means of 
> >compensation.
> 
> Nevertheless, that's not the environment 'Plots' is likely to operate
> in, and it should be designed accordingly.

The design is no longer mine. At the time, it seemed that some system 
involving extra Plots for officers could be worked out, not to 
mention that was around the start of "Capitalism, Ho!" (IIRC).

	Antimatter
	rmorganl@fhcrc.org
	Experienced nonplayer

