> >makes for some extra paperwork for the Cartographor (I guess) but
> >allows a Player to pay a whole bunch of fees at once with one order.

This could be formalised by creating a "Maintenance Account" for each
player - an entity which could own Ergs, whose executor was the Carto-
grapher. Players could transfer Ergs into their Accounts (or even into
each others') whenever they wanted. The Cgr could then execute transfers
from the Accounts to the bank, whenever Maintenance needed to be paid.

